						<h3 class="u-margin-b-200 u-margin-b-300-@lg">Making room for growth</h3>
						<p class="subheading-1 u-color-ash-700 w-100 w-80-@xl u-margin-b-800 u-margin-b-1100-@lg">Questrade was growing quickly, with more product launches on the way. I introduced the <strong class="u-color-plum-500">Start Investing</strong> category to organize our core investing pages under a scalable structure that could accomidate future growth.</p>

						<h3 class="u-margin-b-200 u-margin-b-300-@lg">Consolidating scattered content</h3>
						<p class="subheading-1 u-color-ash-700 w-100 w-80-@xl u-margin-b-800 u-margin-b-1100-@lg">Content about account types was scattered across various pages and often repeated. We brought everything into a dedicated <strong class="u-color-plum-500">Account Types</strong> section to simplify navigation and allow for easier updates as new account options were added.</p>

						<h3 class="u-margin-b-200 u-margin-b-300-@lg">Surfacing a key differentiator</h3>					
						<p class="subheading-1 u-color-ash-700 w-100 w-80-@xl u-margin-b-800 u-margin-b-1100-@lg">Questrade's suite of trading apps and tools was a key differentiator, but it was buried deep under the Self-Directed Investing section. We created a standalone <strong class="u-color-plum-500">Apps & Tools</strong> category to bring this content forward and help users understand Questrades unique value.</p>

						<h3 class="u-margin-b-200 u-margin-b-300-@lg">Turning low-performing space into real value</h3>				
						<p class="subheading-1 u-color-ash-700 w-100 w-80-@xl u-margin-b-800 u-margin-b-1100-@lg">The About Us menu saw low engagement, with most traffic going to programs and promotions. We replaced it with <strong class="u-color-plum-500">Ways to Save</strong>, a value-focused section that highlights offers and features like Questrade Plus and Questrade Reserve.</p>						

						<h3 class="u-margin-b-200 u-margin-b-300-@lg">Putting it all together</h3>		
						<p class="subheading-1 u-color-ash-700 w-100 w-80-@xl">Once our IA was validated (through more tree testing), I led the design of new header, footer and mega nav components.</p>							
